03-04 November - Piccata

- 1   lb meat, cutlet style
- 1/2 cup flour
- 1/2 stick butter or margarine
- 2   teaspoon olive oil
- 4   tablespoon sherry or water
-     salt, pepper, paprika to taste
- 3   tablespoon lemon juice
-     lemon slices
- 2   tablespoon drained capers
- 1/4 cup minced parsley 

Pat cutlets with paper towels. Combine flour and spices. Dip cutlets into seasoned flour. Heat butter and oil in skillet until bubbly. Saute cutlets 1 1/2 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towel. Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of oil and butter. Over high heat stir in sherry or water into drippings, scraping skillet to loosen brown bits. Add lemon juice and heat 1 minutes. Return cutlets to skillet, add lemon slices and heat until sauce thickens, about 1 1/2 minute. Add capers and parsley, serve immediately. 